ily_connection","link_text":"Archibald Romaine Mansfield"}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"Tore ACL freshman year, then Olympic medalist","body":"After tearing her ACL at the end of her first year at Middlebury College, Lea Davison rehabbed back to the highest level of competitive cycling — twice racing the Olympics. She competed at London 2012 (11th) and Rio 2016 (7th) in cross-country mountain biking, winning silver at the 2016 UCI World Championships and bronze at 2014."},{"number":2,"category":"social_reform","header":"After seeing no female cycling community, built one","body":"After seeing a lack of women's community in competitive cycling, Lea Davison co-founded Little Bellas with her sister Sabra Davison and friend Angela Irvine. The nonprofit teaches young girls to mountain bike and has expanded into chapters across the United States."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"Wikipedia: Lea Davison","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lea_Davison"},{"label":"USA Cycling: Lea Davison","url":"http://www.usacycling.org/lea-davison.htm"},{"label":"Lea Davison personal blog 'In the Arena'","url":"http://in-the-arena-leadavison.blogspot.com/"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"lea-davison-1983"},"HD4032":{"id":"HD4032","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Fayston","last_name":"Blair","married_names":[],"gender":"female","display_name":"Fayston Blair"},"birth":{"year":2025,"month":1,"day":5,"state":"Vermont","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":14,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"I00557","mother_id